olive oil
1 bunch broccolini
1 bag green beans
1 clove garlic
½ unit lemon
1 bunch mint
1 pinch chilli flakes
1 block feta cheese

Trim the broccolini and green beans. Finely chop the garlic. Heat a medium frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add the broccolini and green beans with a dash of water and cook, tossing regularly, until just tender, 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

While the greens are cooking, zest the lemon to get a pinch, then slice into wedges. Pick and finely chop the mint leaves.

In a medium bowl, combine the lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice, the chilli flakes (if using) and a pinch of salt and pepper. Add the garlic greens and toss to coat.

Divide the garlic broccolini and green beans between plates. Crumble over the feta and sprinkle with the mint. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.